parts.text:
  The issue is CSS specificity — `.retro-layout .final img` at line 1581 sets **all** images inside `.final` to `96px`, and it was beating my `.final-bot` rule.

Fixed by making the selector more specific:

```css
/* before (overridden by .final img) */
.retro-layout .final-bot {
  width: 300px;
  ...

/* after (higher specificity, wins) */
.retro-layout .final .final-bot {
  width: 300px;
  ...
```

Now the lotus image should actually render at **300px** wide in the final CTA section. Let me know if you want it even larger!

